01:52:53,310 --> 01:52:55,490
So when you touch that button over here,

3124
01:52:55,590 --> 01:52:57,350
the apparatus measures the spin.

3125
01:52:58,970 --> 01:53:01,490
The computer records two things.

3126
01:53:01,730 --> 01:53:04,130
It records the state vector,

3127
01:53:04,210 --> 01:53:05,210
the state vector of the spin.

3128
01:53:05,430 --> 01:53:06,290
How does it do that?

3129
01:53:06,590 --> 01:53:09,090
By providing two complex numbers.

3130
01:53:09,830 --> 01:53:12,230
Stored in the computer are two complex numbers,

3131
01:53:12,510 --> 01:53:14,450
alpha up and alpha down,

3132
01:53:15,189 --> 01:53:17,570
subject to the constraint that alpha star alpha

3133
01:53:17,570 --> 01:53:19,750
plus alpha star alpha is equal to one.

3134
01:53:21,110 --> 01:53:23,930
So it stores an information which is equivalent

3135
01:53:23,930 --> 01:53:26,090
to the state vector of the spin.

3136
01:53:26,470 --> 01:53:29,250
And the other thing it stores is the direction

3137
01:53:29,250 --> 01:53:30,970
that you point the apparatus.

3138
01:53:30,970 --> 01:53:33,210
You can move the apparatus

3139
01:53:33,210 --> 01:53:35,450
around by playing with the computer.

3140
01:53:35,610 --> 01:53:36,630
Not move it around,

3141
01:53:36,630 --> 01:53:38,010
but you can reorient it

3142
01:53:38,010 --> 01:53:39,690
in any direction that you like.

3143
01:53:41,030 --> 01:53:42,670
You start with a spin up.

3144
01:53:42,910 --> 01:53:46,150
Now this spin might be interacting with a magnetic field

3145
01:53:46,150 --> 01:53:47,610
or whatever's happening to it.

3146
01:53:47,950 --> 01:53:50,510
The computer solves the Schrodinger equation.

3147
01:53:51,070 --> 01:53:53,790
And solving the Schrodinger equation for the spin,

3148
01:53:53,910 --> 01:53:56,650
that means it updates the state of the spin.

3149
01:53:57,050 --> 01:53:58,910
You start with a particular state,

3150
01:53:59,070 --> 01:54:00,210
doesn't matter what it is,

3151
01:54:00,210 --> 01:54:03,190
and after a time t it updates the spin,

3152
01:54:03,390 --> 01:54:04,769
it updates the state,

3153
01:54:04,930 --> 01:54:07,590
so the computer now knows what alpha is

3154
01:54:07,590 --> 01:54:10,309
after a certain time has elapsed.

3155
01:54:10,830 --> 01:54:12,590
Then you punch the measure button.

3156
01:54:13,729 --> 01:54:17,950
And the computer takes the state,

3157
01:54:18,149 --> 01:54:20,630
turns it into a pair of probabilities,

3158
01:54:21,070 --> 01:54:22,710
alpha star alpha up,

3159
01:54:22,710 --> 01:54:24,010
alpha star alpha down.

3160
01:54:24,350 --> 01:54:28,229
The computer now knows the probability for up and down.

3161
01:54:28,790 --> 01:54:30,189
And it also has a range.

3162
01:54:30,210 --> 01:54:31,130
It has a random number generator.

3163
01:54:31,850 --> 01:54:34,250
Random number generators are a dime a dozen,

3164
01:54:34,390 --> 01:54:35,430
and they work very well.

3165
01:54:35,729 --> 01:54:37,410
With a random number generator,

3166
01:54:37,790 --> 01:54:41,350
it then takes the probabilities alpha up and alpha down,

3167
01:54:41,490 --> 01:54:44,050
and spits out a number plus or minus one

3168
01:54:44,050 --> 01:54:49,570
with probability alpha star alpha and alpha star alpha.

3169
01:54:49,890 --> 01:54:52,350
So it just simulates the quantum mechanics

3170
01:54:52,350 --> 01:54:54,609
by having a random number generator

3171
01:54:55,309 --> 01:54:59,990
that either spits out plus one or minus one,

3172
01:54:59,990 --> 01:55:03,570
but with a probability that's given by alpha star alpha.

3173
01:55:04,130 --> 01:55:06,689
But then the computer then,

3174
01:55:06,769 --> 01:55:08,330
whatever the answer is,

3175
01:55:08,609 --> 01:55:11,490
whatever the answer that the apparatus spit out,

3176
01:55:11,649 --> 01:55:14,630
the computer then updates once again

3177
01:55:14,630 --> 01:55:15,950
the state of the spin

3178
01:55:15,950 --> 01:55:18,520
and says it is in

3179
01:55:18,520 --> 01:55:21,090
the state that the apparatus measured.

3180
01:55:21,490 --> 01:55:23,530
So if the apparatus spits

3181
01:55:23,530 --> 01:55:25,570
out plus one along some axis,

3182
01:55:25,990 --> 01:55:28,490
you get to turn the apparatus,

3183
01:55:31,529 --> 01:55:35,010
but when you get to turn the apparatus,

3184
01:55:35,250 --> 01:55:37,490
you have to do a slightly complicated calculation

3185
01:55:37,490 --> 01:55:40,070
to find out what the statistics are.

3186
01:55:40,330 --> 01:55:41,390
But once you've done it,

3187
01:55:42,150 --> 01:55:43,690
whatever the answer is,

3188
01:55:44,450 --> 01:55:46,420
the computer goes back and

3189
01:55:46,420 --> 01:55:48,390
updates the state of the spin

3190
01:55:48,390 --> 01:55:51,450
to make it consistent with what the apparatus measured.

3191
01:55:51,590 --> 01:55:52,210
You can do this.

3192
01:55:52,370 --> 01:55:54,010
You can try to write a program.

3193
01:55:54,210 --> 01:55:56,390
There's a program that could be written.

3194
01:55:56,470 --> 01:55:58,270
It's probably not even terribly complicated.

3195
01:55:59,250 --> 01:55:59,770
And...

3196
01:55:59,990 --> 01:56:04,250
if you only got to look at the measuring button,

3197
01:56:04,450 --> 01:56:05,450
decide to measure,

3198
01:56:05,590 --> 01:56:06,790
and look at the outcome,

3199
01:56:07,070 --> 01:56:09,910
you would get everything exactly equivalent

3200
01:56:09,910 --> 01:56:12,170
to the extent that a random number generator

3201
01:56:12,170 --> 01:56:14,630
can be a good faithful random number generator.

3202
01:56:14,950 --> 01:56:16,660
You would completely simulate the

3203
01:56:16,660 --> 01:56:18,370
quantum mechanics of the system.

3204
01:56:19,650 --> 01:56:22,650
The lesson is that quantum mechanics can be

3205
01:56:22,650 --> 01:56:24,870
a special case of classical physics.

3206
01:56:25,210 --> 01:56:26,170
So what's going on?

3207
01:56:26,330 --> 01:56:26,790
What the...

3208
01:56:26,790 --> 01:56:28,160
If quantum mechanics can be

3209
01:56:28,160 --> 01:56:29,530
a special case of classical mechanics,

3210
01:56:29,530 --> 01:56:32,810
what's all this confusion

3211
01:56:32,810 --> 01:56:36,950
about quantum mechanics being logically different?

3212
01:56:37,310 --> 01:56:37,910
All right.

3213
01:56:38,150 --> 01:56:40,430
Now we want to play the same game

3214
01:56:41,470 --> 01:56:42,750
with a pair of spins.

3215
01:56:43,350 --> 01:56:44,430
I just have one question.

3216
01:56:44,570 --> 01:56:45,990
You said that quantum mechanics...

3217
01:56:45,990 --> 01:56:47,770
You were trying to say quantum

3218
01:56:47,770 --> 01:56:49,550
mechanics is a special case of classical...

3219
01:56:49,550 --> 01:56:51,530
But I thought in classical everything was deterministic

3220
01:56:51,530 --> 01:56:53,150
in introducing probability.

3221
01:56:53,430 --> 01:56:53,650
Okay,

3222
01:56:53,650 --> 01:56:54,070
but it's...

3223
01:56:54,070 --> 01:56:54,510
Yeah,

3224
01:56:54,510 --> 01:56:54,710
yeah,

3225
01:56:54,710 --> 01:56:54,770
yeah.

3226
01:56:55,290 --> 01:56:56,550
But it's only...

3227
01:56:56,550 --> 01:56:58,150
This is a classical computer,

3228
01:56:58,150 --> 01:57:00,490
and it's using a classical number generator,

3229
01:57:00,770 --> 01:57:02,510
a classical random number generator.

3230
01:57:02,790 --> 01:57:03,190
All right?

3231
01:57:03,230 --> 01:57:05,010
So you do have to add in...

3232
01:57:05,010 --> 01:57:07,790
But the difference between quantum mechanics

3233
01:57:07,790 --> 01:57:10,330
and classical mechanics isn't randomness.

3234
01:57:10,410 --> 01:57:12,870
You can generate all sorts of random number generators

3235
01:57:12,870 --> 01:57:14,680
that would easily fool you

3236
01:57:14,680 --> 01:57:16,490
into thinking they were really random.

3237
01:57:16,890 --> 01:57:17,610
Of course,

3238
01:57:17,610 --> 01:57:19,310
any real random number generator,

3239
01:57:19,590 --> 01:57:21,690
the numbers come from somewheres,

3240
01:57:21,730 --> 01:57:23,270
so they're not strictly random.

3241
01:57:23,590 --> 01:57:26,650
But you can sure make a random number generator

3242
01:57:26,650 --> 01:57:27,510
that would fool anybody.

3243
01:57:27,510 --> 01:57:28,250
So,

3244
01:57:28,250 --> 01:57:30,190
yeah,

3245
01:57:30,190 --> 01:57:33,730
you can build a computer program

3246
01:57:33,730 --> 01:57:36,230
to simulate the quantum mechanics

3247
01:57:36,230 --> 01:57:38,250
basically of any system that you like

3248
01:57:38,250 --> 01:57:40,930
by the same method.

3249
01:57:41,570 --> 01:57:42,030
Okay?

3250
01:57:42,150 --> 01:57:44,470
But now supposing you wanted to simulate

3251
01:57:45,270 --> 01:57:47,730
a system consisting of two electrons.

3252
01:57:48,010 --> 01:57:48,790
There's two electrons,

3253
01:57:48,790 --> 01:57:49,810
two boxes here.

3254
01:57:50,070 --> 01:57:52,750
And you wanted to do it with two computers,

3255
01:57:54,330 --> 01:57:57,490
and in the process of taking the electrons apart,

3256
01:57:57,510 --> 01:57:58,390
you want to take the electrons apart from each other,

3257
01:57:58,470 --> 01:58:01,030
so as to ask this question about the...

3258
01:58:01,030 --> 01:58:02,270
You want to take the computers,

3259
01:58:02,570 --> 01:58:05,050
you want to encode the information

3260
01:58:05,050 --> 01:58:08,330
about Alice's spin in one computer

3261
01:58:08,330 --> 01:58:11,490
and Bob's spin in the other computer,

3262
01:58:11,590 --> 01:58:13,510
physically separate them,

3263
01:58:13,670 --> 01:58:14,790
and ask,

3264
01:58:14,790 --> 01:58:18,950
can these computers simulate quantum mechanics?

3265
01:58:19,090 --> 01:58:20,410
So I'll tell you what the answer is.

3266
01:58:20,670 --> 01:58:25,110
As long as the spins

3267
01:58:27,510 --> 01:58:29,210
as long as they start in a product state

3268
01:58:29,210 --> 01:58:30,890
and they don't interact with each other

3269
01:58:30,890 --> 01:58:32,650
and therefore stay in a product state,

3270
01:58:32,930 --> 01:58:34,150
then you can do it.

3271
01:58:34,410 --> 01:58:36,430
You can put all of the information

3272
01:58:37,549 --> 01:58:39,570
about Bob's spin in here,

3273
01:58:39,770 --> 01:58:42,850
all the information about Alice's spin in here.

3274
01:58:43,430 --> 01:58:43,950
Likewise,

3275
01:58:43,950 --> 01:58:46,690
you can have Bob's apparatus over here,

3276
01:58:46,850 --> 01:58:49,630
you can have Alice's apparatus over here,

3277
01:58:49,710 --> 01:58:50,610
little black boxes,

3278
01:58:50,750 --> 01:58:54,690
and it's just basically two identical versions

3279
01:58:55,450 --> 01:58:56,530
of what I said before.

3280
01:58:57,730 --> 01:58:59,290
You can take the computers,

3281
01:58:59,290 --> 01:59:00,790
physically separate them,

3282
01:59:01,489 --> 01:59:03,410
do experiments on each one,

3283
01:59:03,550 --> 01:59:05,270
and they will completely agree

3284
01:59:05,270 --> 01:59:07,030
with the results of quantum mechanics

3285
01:59:07,030 --> 01:59:09,010
because if they're in a product state,

3286
01:59:09,250 --> 01:59:10,690
one doesn't care about the other.

3287
01:59:11,410 --> 01:59:12,110
But then you say,

3288
01:59:12,110 --> 01:59:14,250
what if I wanted to put these two spins

3289
01:59:14,250 --> 01:59:15,730
in an entangled state?

3290
01:59:16,829 --> 01:59:17,389
Well,

3291
01:59:17,389 --> 01:59:18,530
first of all,

3292
01:59:18,550 --> 01:59:20,630
to put them in an entangled state,

3293
01:59:21,250 --> 01:59:24,330
you cannot do it without bringing the computers together.

3294
01:59:24,950 --> 01:59:26,410
Bringing the computers together

3295
01:59:26,410 --> 01:59:27,930
so that they talk to each other.

3296
01:59:29,190 --> 01:59:32,990
You can record in the combined computer system,

3297
01:59:33,170 --> 01:59:34,270
now that they're brought together,

3298
01:59:35,150 --> 01:59:38,870
how many numbers does it take

3299
01:59:38,870 --> 01:59:42,650
to specify the state of a two-spin system?

3300
01:59:44,810 --> 01:59:45,410
Six.

3301
01:59:46,929 --> 01:59:47,530
So,

3302
01:59:47,530 --> 01:59:50,310
you record six numbers in the computer here.

3303
01:59:51,770 --> 01:59:54,510
Six numbers are recorded in the computer,

3304
01:59:54,510 --> 01:59:58,510
and some numbers to reflect the orientations

3305
01:59:59,230 --> 02:00:05,450
of various apparatuses that you might conceive of.

3306
02:00:05,910 --> 02:00:08,710
And then you try to split the computer into two.

3307
02:00:10,509 --> 02:00:12,990
Keeping Alice's information in here

3308
02:00:12,990 --> 02:00:15,350
and Bob's information in here,

3309
02:00:15,450 --> 02:00:18,450
separate them and try to simulate

3310
02:00:18,450 --> 02:00:22,670
the quantum mechanics of the entangled system.

3311
02:00:23,450 --> 02:00:25,510
Bell's theorem is what tells you

3312
02:00:25,510 --> 02:00:27,070
that you cannot do this

3313
02:00:27,070 --> 02:00:31,630
unless there are instantaneous action

3314
02:00:31,630 --> 02:00:36,070
at a distance phenomena taking place between the com...

3315
02:00:36,070 --> 02:00:37,550
wires between the computer,

3316
02:00:37,550 --> 02:00:38,210
so to speak.

3317
02:00:38,390 --> 02:00:41,130
Hidden wires that have to be part of the system

3318
02:00:41,130 --> 02:00:43,310
connecting the computers together.

3319
02:00:43,510 --> 02:00:48,550
You cannot simulate the quantum mechanics

3320
02:00:48,550 --> 02:00:50,150
with a classical computer system.

3321
02:00:50,310 --> 02:00:52,310
You can't simulate the quantum mechanics

3322
02:00:52,670 --> 02:00:55,110
of an entangled system

3323
02:00:55,670 --> 02:00:59,050
unless it's really just one computer.

3324
02:00:59,590 --> 02:01:00,310
Really,

3325
02:01:00,310 --> 02:01:01,730
one computer means

3326
02:01:01,730 --> 02:01:04,650
that signals can be transmitted back and forth

3327
02:01:04,650 --> 02:01:05,550
basically instantly.

3328
02:01:06,510 --> 02:01:08,270
That's what Bell's theorem really says.

3329
02:01:08,850 --> 02:01:09,210
Now,

3330
02:01:09,210 --> 02:01:12,330
is this a form of nonlocality?

3331
02:01:12,870 --> 02:01:13,230
Well,

3332
02:01:13,230 --> 02:01:15,090
you might think that if to...

3333
02:01:15,590 --> 02:01:18,470
if you really have to have these wires there

3334
02:01:18,470 --> 02:01:20,830
to simulate quantum mechanics,

3335
02:01:20,830 --> 02:01:23,790
then why can't you send an instantaneous message

3336
02:01:23,790 --> 02:01:24,670
through these wires?

3337
02:01:25,130 --> 02:01:25,730
Of course,

3338
02:01:25,730 --> 02:01:26,110
you can.

3339
02:01:26,810 --> 02:01:29,530
But not if you only allow yourself

3340
02:01:29,530 --> 02:01:32,210
to do the things which quantum mechanics permits.

3341
02:01:32,690 --> 02:01:33,710
For example,

3342
02:01:33,710 --> 02:01:34,250
there are things

3343
02:01:34,250 --> 02:01:35,570
that quantum mechanics doesn't permit.

3344
02:01:35,730 --> 02:01:36,810
It doesn't allow you to measure

3345
02:01:36,810 --> 02:01:39,370
the X and Y component of a spin simultaneously.

3346
02:01:40,670 --> 02:01:42,340
All kinds of things that it

3347
02:01:42,340 --> 02:01:44,010
does not permit you to do

3348
02:01:44,010 --> 02:01:46,890
because they correspond to noncommuting operators.

3349
02:01:47,730 --> 02:01:50,110
If you restrict yourself to the measurements

3350
02:01:50,110 --> 02:01:52,510
which quantum mechanics allows you to do

3351
02:01:52,510 --> 02:01:55,150
on either one of these or any combination of them,

3352
02:01:55,310 --> 02:01:58,330
then it's a very magical and special fact

3353
02:01:58,330 --> 02:02:00,790
that you cannot send information

3354
02:02:00,790 --> 02:02:02,090
faster than the speed of light.

3355
02:02:02,150 --> 02:02:04,090
You cannot send information instantaneously

3356
02:02:04,090 --> 02:02:06,530
by this computer setup.

3357
02:02:06,950 --> 02:02:09,390
What if you assign not probabilities

3358
02:02:09,390 --> 02:02:11,290
but conditional probabilities?

3359
02:02:11,810 --> 02:02:12,750
Doesn't matter.

3360
02:02:13,070 --> 02:02:16,370
If you want to simulate a quantum system

3361
02:02:16,370 --> 02:02:19,230
with a classical system of computers,

3362
02:02:19,230 --> 02:02:22,190
and you want to study entangled systems,

3363
02:02:22,530 --> 02:02:25,010
the computers have to be able to communicate

3364
02:02:25,010 --> 02:02:26,650
with each other instantaneously.

3365
02:02:26,890 --> 02:02:29,030
That's the content of Bell's theorem.

3366
02:02:29,850 --> 02:02:30,490
Now,

3367
02:02:30,490 --> 02:02:32,450
does that mean that there's any action,

3368
02:02:32,510 --> 02:02:34,150
a spooky action at a distance,

3369
02:02:34,370 --> 02:02:37,110
or does it just mean that you've gotten yourself

3370
02:02:37,110 --> 02:02:41,110
into trouble by trying to simulate quantum mechanics

3371
02:02:41,110 --> 02:02:42,150
with classical mechanics?

3372
02:02:42,470 --> 02:02:46,130
My view is that you've gotten yourself into trouble

3373
02:02:46,130 --> 02:02:48,230
by trying to simulate something

3374
02:02:48,230 --> 02:02:50,710
which just doesn't want to be described

3375
02:02:50,710 --> 02:02:52,430
by a classical computer system,

3376
02:02:52,630 --> 02:02:54,230
and it's a deep and interesting fact

3377
02:02:54,230 --> 02:02:55,350
about quantum mechanics.

3378
02:02:56,230 --> 02:03:01,810
Einstein's view was that this is basically evidence

3379
02:03:01,810 --> 02:03:05,190
that the description is incomplete

3380
02:03:06,170 --> 02:03:09,750
and that there are other variables of the system,

3381
02:03:09,910 --> 02:03:12,830
and Bell's conclusion was those other variables

3382
02:03:12,830 --> 02:03:16,670
have to be hidden wires that connect distant places.

3383
02:03:19,610 --> 02:03:20,030
So,

3384
02:03:20,030 --> 02:03:24,390
you can take it for however you see it yourself.

3385
02:03:24,670 --> 02:03:24,890
Yes?

3386
02:03:25,450 --> 02:03:27,230
If you had a quantum computer there,

3387
02:03:27,370 --> 02:03:29,570
and let's say when you had the states...

3388
02:03:29,570 --> 02:03:30,850
If you had a quantum computer,

3389
02:03:30,850 --> 02:03:31,650
you could do it.

3390
02:03:31,990 --> 02:03:33,530
And you separated it,

3391
02:03:33,530 --> 02:03:33,990
right?

3392
02:03:34,150 --> 02:03:34,530
Now,

3393
02:03:34,530 --> 02:03:36,410
when you observe Bob's computer,

3394
02:03:36,590 --> 02:03:38,310
now you know something about Alice's,

3395
02:03:38,310 --> 02:03:38,950
right?

3396
02:03:39,350 --> 02:03:40,970
But you can't really still send it...

3397
02:03:40,970 --> 02:03:41,170
No,

